<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cruel1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cruel,</orth> adj. 1) hardhearted, savage: <bibl n="shak. ven 624" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 624</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1460" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1460</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 60.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 60, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.63.10" default="NO" valid="yes">63, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.129.4" default="NO" valid="yes">129, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.131.2" default="NO" valid="yes">131, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.133.5" default="NO" valid="yes">133, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.140.1" default="NO" valid="yes">140, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 269" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 269</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.281" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 281</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.207.281" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.318" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 318</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.217" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 217</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 7</bibl> etc. etc. Substantively: <cit><quote>O c.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 149.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 149, 1</bibl></cit>. Compar. <cit><quote>crueller:</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 2, 71</bibl></cit>. Superl. <cit><quote>cruellest:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.259" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 259</bibl></cit>. -- Followed by <cit><quote>to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 1, 8</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 32</bibl> By <cit><quote>with:</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 27</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) hard, painful: <cit><quote>O c. speeding,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 269" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 269</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a c. fever,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with c. pain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 80</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 12</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 2, 71</bibl>. <cit><quote>you have seen c. proof of this man's strength,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.184" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 184</bibl></cit> etc.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>